body.plain: On this smooth duet, Mereba and J.I.D reflect on a relationship that has terribly soured. They attempt to compromise and reconcile but realize that with each other, they are like a violent “Sandstorm.”

annotations: We were low, we were high, Jekyll, Hyde

Strange Case of Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde is an 1886 book by Robert Louis Stevenson. The novella details an individual who investigates strange occurrences between his good friend, Henry Jekyll, and the evil Edward Hyde, who are later revealed to be one in the same.

The term “Jekyll and Hyde” is now used for people who are usually good but sometimes terribly evil.
So it’s like a sandstorm, when we get to blows

Sand and dust storms are common meteorological hazards in arid and semi-arid regions. They occur when strong winds lift large amounts of sand and dust into the atmosphere, transporting them hundreds to thousands of miles away. The storms are a serious risk to human health, public safety, agriculture, and infrastructure.

Mereba and J.I.D compare the destructiveness of a sandstorm to the violence within their relationship.

“Cool as a cucumber” is a popular idiom that can be best defined as calm and composed. It potentially derives from the fact that the inside of a cucumber remains cooler than the air around it, even in hot weather.

This page highlights the notable singles released in all genres throughout June 2020. Each song title includes a hyperlink to the corresponding lyric page.

Adding songs



If there’s a notable song you think should be listed here, add it! Or add a comment at the bottom of the page if you’re not sure. No self-promotion, please.


Adding lyrics



If you notice that any of the songs on this list haven’t been transcribed, go to the corresponding page and add in lyrics!

If we have any dates wrong, etc, add a comment at the bottom of the page.
